To obtain a source of RVFV and SBV-specific VHHs with potential neutralizing activity for the respective viruses, llamas were inoculated with the live-attenuated RVFV vaccine strain Clone 13, RVFV virus-like particles (VLPs) or SBV NL-F6 (
 Figure 1A). All inoculated animals responded well with virus-specific neutralizing antibodies in serum above a 50% neutralizing titer of 500 (
 Figure 1B; 
 Wichgers Schreur et al., 2017; 
 Loeffen et al., 2012). The B-cell-derived VHH phagemid libraries contained >10
 7 unique clones per animal.
